CatDescriptText: Miss Dorothy Haley, high school senior, 7208 Kedron Street, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 1, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that 18-year-olds should be given the privilege of voting?" answer reads: "No. I don't think that they are grown up enough and, also, they have not been in world long enough to be able to choose wisely."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Dorothy Haley wearing sunglasses and floral blouse or dress, standing in front of Jenkins Arcade, Liberty Avenue, Downtown
